A fire outbreak has destroyed parts of St. Peter’s Minor Seminary, Kateri, Kaduna. Some sections of the building, including the kitchen, dormitory, and dining hall were all burnt down. This was contained in a statement by the Archdiocesan Chancellor of the church, Fr. Christian Emmanuel. The statement, “Further information will be communicated in due course.” Kateri has been noted for tragic incidents such as bandits’ attacks, killings and in most cases, demands for ransom.